The Central Government and relevant departments in Guangdong Province have tightened quarantine controls and offered active assistance to Hong Kong in the battle against bird flu, according to Foreign Ministry spokesman Tang Guoqiang.
Tung Chee Hwa, chief executive of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region, said here Wednesday that the government had closely monitored the avian flu situation.
The measures would include steps raising the standards of sanitation and hygiene in Hong Kong, particularly on the farms, wholesale markets and retail outlets to make people eat chickens again, the papers said.
